Bone traits for male and female AXB/BXA RI strains were compared using a two-way analysis of variance (ANOVA) to test whether mechanical properties and physical bone traits were inherited in a sex-specific manner, similar to prior studies (Orwoll et al. 2001). A direct comparison between sexes was facilitated by converting trait values to Z scores to minimize size effects. A Z score was calculated for each femur as
